the flat world and education how america's commitment to equity will determine our future events at stanford the flat world and education how america's commitment to equity will determine our future facebook twitter email print add to calendar in her new book the flat world and education professor linda darling hammond offers an eye opening wake up call concerning america's future and vividly illustrates what the united states needs to do to build a system of high achieving and equitable schools that ensures every child the right to learn former us secretary of education richard riley notes that professor hammond is one of the education researchers whom i most respect all children must mean all children and this book shows us how to do it when wednesday april 13 2011 3 00 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s where stanford humanities center 424 santa teresa street stanford california 94305 map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags lecture reading sponsor center for comparative studies in race and ethnicity stanford center for opportunity policy in education contact 724 3468 cnqueen stanford edu admission free and open to the public permalink http events stanford edu events 272 27241 more info last modified april 8 2011
